WEBVTT

00:01.871 --> 00:04.208
(crying)

00:04.208 --> 00:06.379
(feet slapping on pavement)

00:06.379 --> 00:08.483
(gasps)

00:08.483 --> 00:10.487
(car engine revving)

00:14.295 --> 00:16.165
(gasping)

00:19.706 --> 00:21.911
(cries)

00:21.911 --> 00:23.179
(shouts)

00:45.959 --> 00:47.896
(electronic guitar
playing loudly)

00:54.977 --> 00:56.914
("Hungry Like the Wolf"
playing badly)

01:01.924 --> 01:03.928
♪ In touch with the ground ♪

01:03.928 --> 01:07.683
♪ I'm on the hunt,
I'm after you ♪

01:07.683 --> 01:08.685
Guys.

01:08.685 --> 01:09.821
♪ Smell like I sound ♪

01:09.821 --> 01:10.756
Guys!

01:10.756 --> 01:12.292
♪ Lost in a crowd... ♪
Guys, guys, guys,

01:12.292 --> 01:13.829
guys, guys, guys.

01:13.829 --> 01:15.432
(in Dutch accent):
Hello, neighbor.

01:15.432 --> 01:17.168
Hello. Look...

01:17.168 --> 01:18.572
I'm not one

01:18.572 --> 01:20.643
to, you know, put the brakes
on a party,

01:20.643 --> 01:23.347
but, uh, well,
it's early and, uh,

01:23.347 --> 01:25.318
you guys can't play or sing,
so...

01:25.318 --> 01:26.588
MAN:
Too early?

01:26.588 --> 01:27.590
No way, man.

01:27.590 --> 01:29.794
It is never too early to rock.

01:29.794 --> 01:31.196
Super fun!

01:31.196 --> 01:32.867
(all whooping)

01:32.867 --> 01:34.671
Right.
This is my wolves.

01:34.671 --> 01:36.240
Uh, amazing.

01:36.240 --> 01:37.476
Uh... well, as you can

01:37.476 --> 01:38.679
tell, uh...

01:38.679 --> 01:40.348
this part of the beach is taken.

01:40.348 --> 01:41.685
So, maybe we could...

01:41.685 --> 01:43.755
you know, rock up the coast.

01:43.755 --> 01:46.761
This is a public beach lot, no?

01:48.632 --> 01:49.701
(under breath):
All right.

01:49.701 --> 01:50.836
So, where are you guys from?

01:50.836 --> 01:52.372
We are from Amsterdam,

01:52.372 --> 01:53.542
here to R‐O‐C‐K

01:53.542 --> 01:54.944
in the U. S. A.

01:54.944 --> 01:56.246
(man laughs)

01:56.246 --> 01:57.248
(electronic guitar playing)

01:57.248 --> 01:58.552
♪ Do, do, do, do, do ♪

01:58.552 --> 02:00.723
♪ Do, do, do, do, do‐do ♪

02:00.723 --> 02:02.225
♪ Do‐do‐do, do‐do ♪

02:02.225 --> 02:04.864
♪ In touch with the ground ♪

02:04.864 --> 02:06.200
♪ I'm on the hunt ♪
(electronic guitar stops)

02:06.200 --> 02:07.068
♪ I'm... ♪

02:11.678 --> 02:14.149
Welcome to
Los Angeles, boys.

02:20.429 --> 02:23.367
Prepare to be amazed.

02:23.367 --> 02:25.371
RJ:
Oh, what? Do we
not look prepared?

02:25.371 --> 02:26.841
Why did we need

02:26.841 --> 02:28.377
a new TV anyway?

02:28.377 --> 02:30.248
TV?
No, TV is what

02:30.248 --> 02:31.418
we used to have.

02:31.418 --> 02:32.787
This is a state‐of‐the‐art,

02:32.787 --> 02:34.289
fully integrated

02:34.289 --> 02:35.859
entertainment network.

02:35.859 --> 02:36.861
(Trish laughs)

02:36.861 --> 02:38.865
It's adorable how you think

02:38.865 --> 02:40.268
you're gonna remember

02:40.268 --> 02:41.738
how all this
works tomorrow.

02:41.738 --> 02:42.807
Okay, Mr. Murtaugh.

02:42.807 --> 02:44.744
From this you can control
the entire system.
Mm.

02:44.744 --> 02:46.313
Uh‐huh.
And while I had access,

02:46.313 --> 02:47.750
I updated
the OS on your

02:47.750 --> 02:49.554
wireless devices
and networked

02:49.554 --> 02:51.290
your photo libraries.
Awesome.

02:51.290 --> 02:52.292
So, I just press

02:52.292 --> 02:53.562
that?
Mm‐hmm.

02:53.562 --> 02:56.701
Hey! Look, honey,
the Murtaughs!

02:56.701 --> 02:57.803
(chuckles)

02:57.803 --> 02:59.707
We look like we should have
our own reality show.

02:59.707 --> 03:02.378
Look how photogenic
this family is.

03:02.378 --> 03:03.515
Very.
Look at that smile.

03:03.515 --> 03:04.584
Oh, my goodness.

03:04.584 --> 03:06.521
(chuckles)

03:06.521 --> 03:07.656
Very photogenic.

03:07.656 --> 03:08.725
Dad!
Roger!

03:08.725 --> 03:09.927
Oh!

03:09.927 --> 03:10.929
Hey, hey, hey!

03:10.929 --> 03:12.533
What did you do?!
Fix that.

03:12.533 --> 03:13.935
What happened?

03:13.935 --> 03:15.939
What?! No!
Dad!
Now it's bigger.

03:15.939 --> 03:17.275
TRISH:
Come on.
MURTAUGH:
Hey, damn it.

03:17.275 --> 03:18.411
Close your eyes!
What'd you do?

03:18.411 --> 03:19.580
You know what?
Get out of my house.

03:19.580 --> 03:20.816
TRISH:
Just...
Stumble...

03:20.816 --> 03:21.818
your ass out!

03:23.889 --> 03:24.824
What are you...

03:24.824 --> 03:25.959
It‐It‐It's a picture.

03:25.959 --> 03:27.295
I just...
A picture?!

03:27.295 --> 03:28.565
I just wanted to, you know,

03:28.565 --> 03:29.700
see how I looked.

03:29.700 --> 03:31.738
Then why'd
you text it?

03:31.738 --> 03:33.575
Give me that!
Riana.
You texted?!

03:33.575 --> 03:35.311
You text that to someone?!

03:35.311 --> 03:36.481
I want the name

03:36.481 --> 03:38.317
and a number. Now!
What?

03:38.317 --> 03:39.987
What? No way.
Riana... Riana!

03:39.987 --> 03:41.491
Uh, no, no, Roger, calm down.

03:41.491 --> 03:42.493
Are you...
okay with this?!

03:42.493 --> 03:43.461
No, but I don't

03:43.461 --> 03:45.331
want her to be ashamed
of her body, either.

03:45.331 --> 03:46.333
Why not?

03:46.333 --> 03:47.736
I'm comfortable with that.

03:47.736 --> 03:50.542
Which is why I will be
the one to talk to her...

03:50.542 --> 03:52.245
after she calms down.

03:54.015 --> 03:55.552
You think
this is funny?

03:55.552 --> 03:57.055
No, I‐I don't.

03:57.055 --> 03:59.059
Which is why
I memorized the number

03:59.059 --> 04:00.762
where she sent that photo to.

04:00.762 --> 04:01.831
Strong.

04:01.831 --> 04:03.602
(laughing):
Kids, right?

04:05.706 --> 04:07.610
♪ ♪

04:09.981 --> 04:11.316
MURTAUGH:
How old is she?

04:11.316 --> 04:12.853
BAILEY:
19. Nina Clausen.

04:12.853 --> 04:13.855
Found half‐naked and dead

04:13.855 --> 04:14.857
on a hood of a Ferrari,

04:14.857 --> 04:17.328
wrecked on a residential
street in Beverly Hills.

04:17.328 --> 04:18.632
Driver was MIA.

04:18.632 --> 04:19.934
SCORSESE:
From the cuts
on her feet,

04:19.934 --> 04:21.604
I'd say she covered
a good distance.

04:21.604 --> 04:24.009
She was running from somebody,
wasn't she?

04:24.009 --> 04:25.746
What is it?
That's not asphalt.

04:25.746 --> 04:26.881
What is that
on her feet?

04:26.881 --> 04:27.883
Don't know yet.

04:27.883 --> 04:29.019
Sent it to the lab.

04:29.019 --> 04:30.622
I mean, where's she from?

04:30.622 --> 04:31.758
Does she go to school?

04:31.758 --> 04:34.362
As far as I can tell,
she moved from North Carolina

04:34.362 --> 04:36.033
to L. A. about six months ago.

04:36.033 --> 04:37.770
Has some modeling
and acting credits.

04:37.770 --> 04:39.372
MURTAUGH:
That's the same girl?

04:39.372 --> 04:41.411
She looks closer to 17.

04:41.411 --> 04:43.380
RIGGS:
Who's the vehicle
registered to?

04:43.380 --> 04:44.517
No registered
owner or plate,

04:44.517 --> 04:45.686
just a license frame

04:45.686 --> 04:47.389
from a place
called Prime Exotics.

04:47.389 --> 04:50.662
Hey, Bail.

04:50.662 --> 04:52.533
I'm gonna send you
a phone number.

04:52.533 --> 04:55.739
I need you to get me whatever
you can on whoever it is.

04:55.739 --> 04:57.810
It's not about the
case; it's personal.

05:00.549 --> 05:02.753
The city of dreams, huh?

05:02.753 --> 05:05.492
(rap song playing)

05:12.673 --> 05:16.781
Man, how small does
your penis need to be

05:16.781 --> 05:19.520
to buy one
of these cars?

05:19.520 --> 05:21.791
Gentlemen,
welcome to Prime Exotics,

05:21.791 --> 05:23.862
where car dreams
become reality.

05:23.862 --> 05:25.932
I own one of these
bad boys myself.

05:25.932 --> 05:27.669
Wonderful.

05:27.669 --> 05:29.005
My partner has a question
for you.

05:29.005 --> 05:30.074
Yeah, ask me anything.

05:30.074 --> 05:31.276
Joseph O'Brien,
head of sales.

05:31.276 --> 05:36.587
Are these cars absolutely
perfect for Los Angeles or what?

05:36.587 --> 05:38.958
Yeah... listen, I'm LAPD.

05:38.958 --> 05:40.429
I need some information
on one of your customers.

05:40.429 --> 05:41.431
Someone who bought

05:41.431 --> 05:43.701
a red F355.

05:43.701 --> 05:46.106
RIGGS:
Uh, a little help here?

05:46.106 --> 05:48.043
♪ ♪

05:48.043 --> 05:49.112
(car beeps)

05:49.112 --> 05:51.016
Ah!

05:52.519 --> 05:53.721
Fancy!

05:53.721 --> 05:54.723
How much for this
one right here?

05:54.723 --> 05:56.461
It's, uh, $210,000.

05:56.461 --> 05:57.996
Make it 205 and I'll take it

05:57.996 --> 05:59.132
off your hands today.

05:59.132 --> 06:00.735
Oh, wait a minute.

06:00.735 --> 06:02.071
No cup holder.

06:02.071 --> 06:03.842
Red F355.

06:03.842 --> 06:05.579
Who bought it?

06:05.579 --> 06:08.016
Look, I'd love to help you guys
out here, but our customers...

06:08.016 --> 06:09.553
uh... they value discretion.

06:09.553 --> 06:11.691
This is a murder
investigation,

06:11.691 --> 06:13.962
so I suggest you tell me
what I need to know

06:13.962 --> 06:15.899
so you can get back
to your little tanning bed.

06:15.899 --> 06:17.836
RIGGS:
Uh, Joseph, do not
listen to him.

06:17.836 --> 06:19.507
You are bronzed, beautiful...

06:19.507 --> 06:20.575
(clucks tongue)
... and powerful.

06:20.575 --> 06:21.878
Hey, Joey.

06:21.878 --> 06:22.980
Let's go for a test ride.

06:22.980 --> 06:24.115
(Murtaugh laughs)

06:24.115 --> 06:25.852
I wouldn't do that if I was you.

06:25.852 --> 06:27.389
Ah, come on, Joey!

06:27.389 --> 06:28.725
Be somebody.
Sell a car today, my man.

06:38.478 --> 06:40.482
JOSEPH:
<i>What‐What‐What are you doing?</i>

06:40.482 --> 06:41.884
Slow down!

06:41.884 --> 06:43.655
Ah, I'm sorry.
I am in a mood.

06:43.655 --> 06:44.757
Had a rough morning.

06:44.757 --> 06:45.892
I got new neighbors,
Dutch accents,

06:45.892 --> 06:47.028
<i>but then there's you, Joe.</i>

06:47.028 --> 06:48.130
<i>You know?</i>
<i>And I just don't feel like</i>

06:48.130 --> 06:49.900
<i>you're meeting me halfway</i>
<i>on things.</i>

06:49.900 --> 06:51.169
I mean, look, sales
is a two‐way street.

06:51.169 --> 06:52.506
Am I right?

06:52.506 --> 06:53.841
♪ I wanna be a superhero ♪

06:54.910 --> 06:57.649
(car horns beeping)

06:57.649 --> 06:58.818
J‐J‐Just‐Just let me out.
Please!

06:58.818 --> 07:00.522
Oh, hop out any time.

07:00.522 --> 07:01.457
Or...

07:01.457 --> 07:02.726
you can tell me who purchased

07:02.726 --> 07:04.597
that F355.

07:04.597 --> 07:05.732
Red light,
red light!

07:05.732 --> 07:07.134
(car horn beeping)

07:07.134 --> 07:08.871
(Joseph screams)

07:08.871 --> 07:10.609
Okay, okay!
It was Dylan Ashworth!

07:10.609 --> 07:11.911
There it is.

07:14.148 --> 07:16.621
He's insane.

07:16.621 --> 07:18.658
RIGGS:
So, I got the name.

07:19.760 --> 07:21.897
Dylan Ashworth.

07:21.897 --> 07:23.501
So did I...

07:23.501 --> 07:24.503
from Rick here.

07:24.503 --> 07:26.507
And all I had to do was ask.

07:26.507 --> 07:27.976
Well, thank you, Rick...

07:27.976 --> 07:29.178
for everything.

07:29.178 --> 07:31.517
You know, I love
this town...

07:31.517 --> 07:33.788
sometimes.

07:33.788 --> 07:35.692
♪ ♪

07:38.798 --> 07:40.702
Are you two aware
that Dylan Ashworth

07:40.702 --> 07:42.606
is Henry Ashworth's son?

07:42.606 --> 07:44.743
And Sheldon and Dorothy
Ashworth's grandson,

07:44.743 --> 07:45.945
yeah, we get it.

07:45.945 --> 07:47.549
Uh, I have no idea
who these people are.

07:47.549 --> 07:49.553
Have you ever driven
on Ashworth Boulevard?

07:49.553 --> 07:50.488
Or been to
Ashworth Pavilion?

07:50.488 --> 07:51.957
You know, I don't
frequent pavilions,

07:51.957 --> 07:52.959
not as much as I should,

07:52.959 --> 07:54.563
and I know that
I'm missing out,

07:54.563 --> 07:56.232
but I...
You ever heard
of Ashworth, California?

07:56.232 --> 07:57.836
What, do they got
their own city?

07:57.836 --> 07:59.238
It's where the family
struck gold,

07:59.238 --> 08:01.109
literally, back in 1849.

08:01.109 --> 08:04.048
They've been California
royalty ever since.

08:04.048 --> 08:05.652
That doesn't make them
above the law.

08:05.652 --> 08:08.591
No, but they do keep
an entire law firm on retainer.

08:08.591 --> 08:10.662
Well, good.
If this Dylan kid

08:10.662 --> 08:12.532
murdered our girl
then he's gonna need it.

08:12.532 --> 08:14.135
Let's go have a chat with him.

08:14.135 --> 08:16.841
Agreed, but just talk to him.

08:16.841 --> 08:18.811
The Ashworths
are formidable.

08:18.811 --> 08:20.114
Keep it completely professional,
respectful even.

08:21.851 --> 08:22.953
Why are you just looking at me?

08:22.953 --> 08:24.890
Because you are the only one
that I am talking to.

08:26.560 --> 08:29.098
♪ ♪

08:41.122 --> 08:43.126
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

08:43.126 --> 08:45.899
♪ Get low when
the whistle blow... ♪

08:50.073 --> 08:52.546
Cover it up, ladies.

08:52.546 --> 08:54.015
♪ Get, get, get, get low... ♪

08:58.023 --> 08:59.760
Hi there, cutie.

08:59.760 --> 09:01.630
I love your mustache.
Oh.

09:01.630 --> 09:03.233
Thank you very much.
Be careful, though,

09:03.233 --> 09:04.837
a couple of drinks
and it gets kind of crazy.

09:04.837 --> 09:06.640
That's my kind of mustache.

09:06.640 --> 09:08.109
(chuckles)
Can I get it, or you,

09:08.109 --> 09:10.582
a drink?
Or anything else?

09:10.582 --> 09:12.251
Anything?
Mm‐hmm.

09:12.251 --> 09:13.855
That doesn't really narrow
it down, now does it?

09:13.855 --> 09:15.257
That's the idea
at these parties.

09:15.257 --> 09:17.027
Ah, who's idea is that?

09:17.027 --> 09:18.029
Dylan?

09:18.029 --> 09:19.733
Well, it's Dylan's place,

09:19.733 --> 09:21.537
but it's Julian's party.

09:28.885 --> 09:30.087
Rachel?

09:37.167 --> 09:38.169
♪ Get, get, get... ♪

09:38.169 --> 09:40.173
Excuse me.

09:40.173 --> 09:41.644
♪ Get, get, get, get low ♪

09:41.644 --> 09:43.213
♪ When the whistle blow... ♪

09:45.083 --> 09:48.056
Mr. Ashworth.

09:48.056 --> 09:49.058
Who are you?

09:49.058 --> 09:51.664
Detective
Roger Murtaugh, LAPD.

09:51.664 --> 09:53.668
What, are you part of the
security detail for the party?

09:53.668 --> 09:54.469
Talk to Julian.

09:54.469 --> 09:56.205
He handles all that.
No, I'm here

09:56.205 --> 09:58.209
investigating a homicide.

09:58.209 --> 10:00.213
Young lady named
Ms. Nina Clausen.

10:00.213 --> 10:02.151
Does that name
ring a bell?

10:02.151 --> 10:03.621
Nope.

10:03.621 --> 10:05.023
Was she hot?

10:06.125 --> 10:07.294
She was found dead

10:07.294 --> 10:08.898
on the hood of a wrecked Ferrari

10:08.898 --> 10:11.135
that you bought
about six weeks ago.

10:11.135 --> 10:12.706
Is the car okay?

10:12.706 --> 10:14.108
(Dylan chuckles)

10:14.108 --> 10:16.747
I think it would be
in your best interest

10:16.747 --> 10:17.849
if we went somewhere

10:17.849 --> 10:20.320
where we could talk
about this very sensitive matter

10:20.320 --> 10:21.724
in private.

10:21.724 --> 10:23.159
All right.
(groaning)

10:23.159 --> 10:24.195
You're under arrest

10:24.195 --> 10:25.263
for possession of narcotics.

10:25.263 --> 10:26.265
Come on.
Let me go!

10:26.265 --> 10:27.769
Damn it!
Get your ass in there.

10:27.769 --> 10:28.738
Are you kidding me?!

10:31.142 --> 10:32.746
RIGGS:
Rachel!

10:37.889 --> 10:39.693
Do you have any idea
who you're messing with?

10:39.693 --> 10:40.895
I do.

10:40.895 --> 10:43.434
Detective Riggs,
meet Dylan Ashworth.

10:43.434 --> 10:45.170
Now he does, too.

10:45.170 --> 10:47.174
Hey.
Hmm?

10:47.174 --> 10:48.844
You all right?

10:48.844 --> 10:50.313
I just saw somebody
I knew.

10:50.313 --> 10:52.485
Doesn't seem like this is
your kind of scene.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.255
No, it was a friend
of Miranda's

10:54.255 --> 10:55.925
Her old roommate.

10:55.925 --> 10:57.796
I'll have both
your badges.

10:57.796 --> 10:58.931
BOTH:
Shut up!

10:58.931 --> 10:59.933
Get out of here.

11:09.193 --> 11:11.824
Hi, everyone. Rachel.

11:11.824 --> 11:13.808
Uh, I hate giving speeches,

11:13.808 --> 11:16.948
but there is one story
I'd like to tell.

11:16.948 --> 11:20.088
So Miranda and I
were living together

11:20.088 --> 11:23.628
when she booked a job
in Texas.

11:23.628 --> 11:25.866
And I get a phone call
from her,

11:25.866 --> 11:29.640
and she says that she's
gonna be staying a little longer

11:29.640 --> 11:31.577
'cause she met a guy...
(chuckles)

11:31.577 --> 11:33.515
... and could I send her
some clothes?

11:33.515 --> 11:36.019
I said, "Sure.
What do you need?"

11:36.019 --> 11:37.856
And she said,
"Cowboy boots."

11:37.856 --> 11:40.061
(scattered laughter)

11:40.061 --> 11:44.002
I knew in that moment
that I lost her forever.

11:44.002 --> 11:47.142
Um, Martin, I don't know what
you did or how you did it...

11:47.142 --> 11:48.278
(acoustic music playing)

11:48.278 --> 11:50.782
... but Miranda is happier
than I have ever seen her.

11:50.782 --> 11:53.488
(acoustic music continues)

11:53.488 --> 11:55.625
(men singing off‐key)
♪ In touch with the ground ♪

11:55.625 --> 11:59.099
♪ I'm on the hunt,
I'm after you ♪

11:59.099 --> 12:02.105
♪ Smell like I sound,
lost in a crowd ♪

12:02.105 --> 12:08.117
♪ And I'm hungry
like the wolf... ♪

12:08.117 --> 12:11.724
Hey, <i>lamzak.</i>

12:11.724 --> 12:13.862
Check it out.

12:13.862 --> 12:15.732
No power, no problem.

12:15.732 --> 12:21.043
Do you guys know
any, um... Bluto Blutarsky?

12:21.043 --> 12:23.481
Blu...

12:23.481 --> 12:25.485
Who?
Are you serious?
You guys don't know...

12:25.485 --> 12:28.023
Oh, he's amazing.
Really amazing, yeah.

12:28.023 --> 12:29.025
May I?

12:29.025 --> 12:30.762
Yeah, okay.

12:30.762 --> 12:31.764
Play it, man.

12:31.764 --> 12:34.036
Thank you.

12:34.036 --> 12:36.407
(tuning)

12:42.653 --> 12:44.924
(exclaiming)

12:49.533 --> 12:51.537
