26:25.558 --> 26:27.964
Because I'm from Wisconsin.

26:27.964 --> 26:30.335
I don't know the names
of anyone else.

26:32.039 --> 26:33.274
Thank you.

26:33.274 --> 26:35.512
If I can figure out the code of
Dylan Ashworth, I can prove

26:35.512 --> 26:37.316
that he was with Nina
the night she was killed.

26:37.316 --> 26:39.186
He wasn't.

26:43.461 --> 26:44.496
How do you know?

26:44.496 --> 26:46.935
Because he was with me.

26:48.004 --> 26:49.206
All night.

26:49.206 --> 26:51.377
(sniffling)

26:53.614 --> 26:55.485
(voice breaking):
Just leave.

26:55.485 --> 26:57.022
Please?

27:03.701 --> 27:06.073
(sniffles)
(door closes)

27:08.177 --> 27:10.081
(dog barking in distance)

27:11.317 --> 27:13.221
(knocking at door)

27:17.062 --> 27:19.333
Hello, sugar.

27:19.333 --> 27:22.472
I am so sorry I didn't call,
but surprises are fun,

27:22.472 --> 27:24.343
right?

27:24.343 --> 27:25.545
You all right?

27:25.545 --> 27:27.616
Yeah. Just...

27:27.616 --> 27:29.219
been a tough day.
(sighs)

27:29.219 --> 27:30.622
We've all have those.

27:30.622 --> 27:32.092
Luckily though, I know

27:32.092 --> 27:33.628
just the cure for tough days.

27:33.628 --> 27:35.766
(whispering):
Fantastic nights.

27:35.766 --> 27:36.868
Right.

27:36.868 --> 27:39.673
Thanks, but I'm not really
in the mood for a party.

27:41.778 --> 27:43.681
Sure you are.

27:48.850 --> 27:50.119
SCORSESE:
Detective, you came.

27:50.119 --> 27:51.256
Only because you said

27:51.256 --> 27:52.558
you had something to show me.

27:52.558 --> 27:54.228
Look, I get it.

27:54.228 --> 27:56.699
This place
creeps you out.

27:56.699 --> 27:57.835
It's not just the place.

27:57.835 --> 27:58.770
Ouch.

28:00.039 --> 28:01.041
So, what you got?

28:01.041 --> 28:02.645
The lab results came back

28:02.645 --> 28:04.649
on the substance on
Nina Clausen's feet.

28:04.649 --> 28:05.517
Tree sap.

28:05.517 --> 28:08.924
From a Red Dawn Full
Moon Japanese Maple.

28:08.924 --> 28:10.794
Are you making that name up?

28:10.794 --> 28:12.831
No. Very rare.

28:12.831 --> 28:14.201
I ran a search
on any murders

28:14.201 --> 28:16.205
in which victims were
found with similar sap.

28:16.205 --> 28:18.944
Three turned up.
All unsolved.

28:18.944 --> 28:22.217
All women, all
with bruising

28:22.217 --> 28:23.553
on their wrists.

28:23.553 --> 28:25.757
Wow. That's impressive.

28:27.227 --> 28:28.964
<i>Fin.</i>

28:28.964 --> 28:30.834
That's "the end."

28:30.834 --> 28:32.571
In‐in French.

28:32.571 --> 28:35.109
You know,
genius is rarely understood

28:35.109 --> 28:36.279
at first blush.

28:36.279 --> 28:38.516
(elevator bell dings)

28:38.516 --> 28:41.756
Damn, so there's
four victims?
Yeah.

28:41.756 --> 28:44.027
Okay, get me whatever you can
on each one of the cases.

28:44.027 --> 28:44.996
I got you.

28:46.933 --> 28:47.801
Oh, my God.

28:47.801 --> 28:49.271
Hey, baby!
What brings you to the office?

28:49.271 --> 28:51.275
Chauncey Perkins.

28:51.275 --> 28:52.745
Please tell me you didn't...

28:52.745 --> 28:54.281
It wasn't my idea,
it was Riggs' idea.

28:54.281 --> 28:55.617
I just wanted to scare him,

28:55.617 --> 28:57.020
just rough him up a...

28:57.020 --> 28:58.289
Rough him up? He's 19, Roger!

28:58.289 --> 29:00.293
MURTAUGH:
Exactly! Technically,

29:00.293 --> 29:01.295
he's an adult.

29:01.295 --> 29:02.231
A 19‐year‐old

29:02.231 --> 29:04.702
who you threatened
into committing a crime!

29:04.702 --> 29:06.639
MURTAUGH:
It was a misdemeanor,

29:06.639 --> 29:07.541
not a felony.

29:07.541 --> 29:10.847
Do you know he goes
by the name of C‐Dawg?

29:10.847 --> 29:11.849
His parents called me.

29:11.849 --> 29:13.186
(scoffs):
Snitch.

29:13.186 --> 29:14.855
And he broke up with Ri.

29:14.855 --> 29:16.859
And mind you, she is
less upset about him

29:16.859 --> 29:18.730
than she is ashamed
of her father.

29:18.730 --> 29:20.132
But he really broke up with her?

29:20.132 --> 29:22.136
Roger...
Do you know

29:22.136 --> 29:24.742
that he posted her picture‐‐
<i>the</i> picture‐‐

29:24.742 --> 29:26.746
on his Facebook page?

29:26.746 --> 29:28.883
He did?
Uh‐huh. And when

29:28.883 --> 29:30.754
I told him I'm Riana's dad,

29:30.754 --> 29:33.827
he said, "Which Riana?"

29:33.827 --> 29:35.297
Followed by,

29:35.297 --> 29:38.168
"I got a few."
As <i>if</i>

29:38.168 --> 29:41.642
he's got a whole posse
of girls named...

29:41.642 --> 29:42.644
Okay, listen.

29:42.644 --> 29:44.114
I get it.

29:44.114 --> 29:46.185
I'm gonna have a little chat
with C‐Dawg.

29:46.185 --> 29:47.788
Don't wait up for me.

29:47.788 --> 29:50.059
It's okay, Trish,
I already handled it.

29:50.059 --> 29:51.796
"I got a few."
That's what he said?

29:51.796 --> 29:52.865
Yeah.

29:52.865 --> 29:54.134
Hell to the no!

29:54.134 --> 29:55.604
Hey Trish, don't go do nothing

29:55.604 --> 29:57.674
that I have to arrest you for.

29:57.674 --> 29:59.144
Not that I would ever
arrest you.

30:00.280 --> 30:01.749
You go ahead and
commit crime

30:01.749 --> 30:02.818
at will, baby.

30:06.959 --> 30:09.832
Bailey, what are you working on?

30:09.832 --> 30:11.836
A lead on the Clausen case.

30:11.836 --> 30:13.706
The names in this book are
all in code.

30:13.706 --> 30:15.977
Like "Madison" for a girl
from Wisconsin.

30:15.977 --> 30:18.115
Dylan Ashworth‐‐
"Enzo," for his cars.

30:18.115 --> 30:19.385
So Dylan Ashworth
is in there?

30:19.385 --> 30:21.255
Can you link him
to Nina Clausen?

30:21.255 --> 30:23.393
No. He was with
another girl that night.

30:23.393 --> 30:25.797
But I do think Nina is in here.

30:25.797 --> 30:27.267
This girl's last entry
in the book

30:27.267 --> 30:28.736
was the night of Nina's murder.

30:28.736 --> 30:29.939
Name is Charlotte.

30:29.939 --> 30:31.275
Wasn't Nina
from North Carolina?

30:31.275 --> 30:32.811
Yeah, but the codename
of the guy that she was with

30:32.811 --> 30:33.680
is "Montana."

30:33.680 --> 30:35.417
Okay, so "Montana."
So, he's from

30:35.417 --> 30:36.819
Billings, Bozeman...

30:36.819 --> 30:38.890
Or it could be anywhere else.
Big Sky,

30:38.890 --> 30:40.760
Yellowstone...
Hannah?

30:40.760 --> 30:43.031
Hannah Montana. Joking.

30:43.031 --> 30:44.902
Or Joe Montana.

30:44.902 --> 30:45.971
The quarterback?

30:45.971 --> 30:49.043
I know who Joe Montana is.
He played for the 49ers.

30:51.181 --> 30:53.853
Named for the Gold Rush.

30:53.853 --> 30:55.924
The Ashworths were
the original 49ers.

30:55.924 --> 30:57.261
But Nina wasn't with Dylan
that night.

30:57.261 --> 30:58.263
So what if Montana

30:58.263 --> 31:00.200
is another Ashworth?

31:00.200 --> 31:02.271
The father, Henry?

31:02.271 --> 31:03.273
It's possible.

31:03.273 --> 31:05.009
Julian could have supplied him
with the girls

31:05.009 --> 31:07.314
and he would have access
to his son's Ferrari.

31:07.314 --> 31:08.416
SCORSESE:
As well as his own

31:08.416 --> 31:09.685
oil fields.

31:09.685 --> 31:10.887
Captain. Bailey.

31:10.887 --> 31:12.457
In an effort to impress
that will,

31:12.457 --> 31:14.027
no doubt, go unnoticed,

31:14.027 --> 31:15.230
I looked into the
other dead women.

31:15.230 --> 31:16.766
One body was

31:16.766 --> 31:19.170
on land owned
by an Ashworth oil subsidiary.

31:19.170 --> 31:20.005
And this...

31:20.005 --> 31:22.444
is the Ashworth estate
in Bel‐Air.

31:22.444 --> 31:23.780
Note the front of the house.

31:23.780 --> 31:25.317
Specifically, the trees.

31:25.317 --> 31:28.189
Red Dawn Full Moon
Japanese Maples.

31:28.189 --> 31:29.224
What does that mean?

31:29.224 --> 31:31.195
It means Henry Ashworth
is probably

31:31.195 --> 31:32.864
our killer.

31:34.802 --> 31:37.207
♪ My old friend ♪

31:37.207 --> 31:41.349
♪ You had to learn ♪

31:41.349 --> 31:44.087
♪ You will get burned ♪

31:44.087 --> 31:47.026
RACHEL:
Why didn't you tell me
we were coming to Dylan's?

31:47.026 --> 31:48.763
Julian, what is this?

31:48.763 --> 31:49.832
This?

31:49.832 --> 31:51.369
This is your evening, darling.

31:51.369 --> 31:53.038
Perhaps longer. Who knows?

31:53.038 --> 31:56.379
But, there is someone
I'd like you to meet.

31:56.379 --> 31:59.117
Dylan's father,
Henry Ashworth.

32:01.389 --> 32:03.226
Pleasure to meet you.

32:10.139 --> 32:11.976
I'm uncomfortable.

32:13.479 --> 32:16.084
I think I'd like to leave.
I'm sorry.

32:16.084 --> 32:17.354
Oh.

32:17.354 --> 32:19.825
Well, I'm sorry to hear that.

32:19.825 --> 32:21.094
Another time, maybe?

32:23.966 --> 32:25.303
Hey, hey.

32:25.303 --> 32:26.505
Are you all right?

32:26.505 --> 32:28.041
You seem a little stressed.

32:28.041 --> 32:30.380
I am. I want to leave. Now.

32:30.380 --> 32:31.515
Yeah, sure, I get that,

32:31.515 --> 32:33.986
but here's the thing,
darling Rach,

32:33.986 --> 32:35.857
this thing is happening.

32:35.857 --> 32:37.994
So, you can either fight it or

32:37.994 --> 32:39.331
you can go with it.
I can assure you, the latter is

32:39.331 --> 32:41.769
much more fun.

32:43.439 --> 32:45.343
(exhales)

32:46.445 --> 32:48.449
(screams)

32:49.551 --> 32:50.820
(muffled screaming)

32:51.922 --> 32:54.026
♪ ♪

33:01.575 --> 33:03.880
Are you an actress?

33:03.880 --> 33:07.052
Have you done
any, uh, S&M?

33:07.052 --> 33:09.157
Roleplay?
No.

33:09.157 --> 33:12.062
I'm sorry,
I just want to go home.

33:12.062 --> 33:14.000
Aw. Don't be sorry.

33:15.904 --> 33:19.043
You're exactly
what I asked Julian for.

33:20.280 --> 33:22.450
(music playing inside)

33:24.153 --> 33:25.890
How you doing, buddy?
We're here to see

33:25.890 --> 33:27.561
Henry Ashworth.

33:27.561 --> 33:29.565
Sorry. It's a private function.

33:29.565 --> 33:30.567
(sighs)

33:30.567 --> 33:32.571
This is awkward.
I'm embarrassed.

33:32.571 --> 33:34.308
Look at us, showing up
without an invitation.

33:34.308 --> 33:35.310
You didn't
get invited?

33:35.310 --> 33:36.245
I got invited.

33:36.245 --> 33:37.314
So, can I be your plus one?

33:37.314 --> 33:39.318
I don't think so. You leave now,

33:39.318 --> 33:41.188
or I'll be forced
to have to call...

33:41.188 --> 33:42.958
Say it. Please say it.
Please say it. Say it.

33:42.958 --> 33:43.960
The police.

33:43.960 --> 33:45.062
(sighs)
Hello!

33:45.062 --> 33:47.334
Oh! We're already here!

33:47.334 --> 33:48.936
You should also know
that we're being recorded

33:48.936 --> 33:50.138
by security cameras.

33:51.408 --> 33:53.412
Where are those
cameras again?

33:53.412 --> 33:55.383
Back there. And up there.

33:56.619 --> 33:57.887
Ah, good.

33:57.887 --> 33:59.358
(grunts)

33:59.358 --> 34:00.893
♪ ♪

34:07.039 --> 34:08.943
♪ ♪

34:18.061 --> 34:19.998
♪ Tell me something that ♪

34:22.203 --> 34:25.610
♪ Tell me something
that I don't know ♪

34:25.610 --> 34:27.947
RACHEL: Help! Please!
Let me out! Please!
(pounding on door)

34:27.947 --> 34:30.953
I don't want to do this! Please!

34:30.953 --> 34:32.490
Mm, don't fight it.

34:32.490 --> 34:33.626
Enjoy it.

34:33.626 --> 34:36.231
♪ Tell me something ♪

34:36.231 --> 34:37.634
Please, help me!

34:37.634 --> 34:39.003
No!

34:40.373 --> 34:42.310
♪ ♪

34:56.271 --> 34:57.540
What the hell?

34:57.540 --> 34:59.611
LAPD. I'm looking
for Henry Ashworth.

34:59.611 --> 35:01.582
You got a warrant?

35:01.582 --> 35:04.254
Judge Groban, I was hoping
you could issue one

35:04.254 --> 35:05.523
right on the spot.

35:05.523 --> 35:06.525
What do you say?

35:09.264 --> 35:11.301
(panting)

35:15.243 --> 35:17.981
♪ Tell me something that
I don't know ♪

35:17.981 --> 35:19.384
(groaning)

35:19.384 --> 35:20.520
♪ Because it seems ♪

35:20.520 --> 35:22.290
♪ Because it seems that ♪

35:22.290 --> 35:24.528
♪ All your rhymes
have got the same flow ♪

35:24.528 --> 35:27.667
No one gave you permission
to be here, Detective.

35:27.667 --> 35:29.571
(grunts)

35:29.571 --> 35:32.277
Now, see, my friend Rachel...

35:32.277 --> 35:34.146
she invited me.

35:34.146 --> 35:35.182
Where is she?

35:35.182 --> 35:37.085
Get your hands off me.

35:37.085 --> 35:38.689
(shouts)

35:38.689 --> 35:41.295
♪ Because it seems that ♪

35:41.295 --> 35:45.035
♪ All your rhymes
have got the same flow ♪

35:45.035 --> 35:46.638
♪ And you know honestly ♪

35:46.638 --> 35:48.709
♪ It's never meant much to me ♪

35:48.709 --> 35:52.049
♪ Tell me something
that I don't know... ♪

35:52.049 --> 35:53.185
Any sign of Ashworth?

35:53.185 --> 35:56.325
My good friend Julian here
was just about to tell us.

35:56.325 --> 35:58.629
You have nothing on me.
Maybe.

35:58.629 --> 36:01.235
But we have four murders
we can pin on Henry Ashworth.

36:01.235 --> 36:02.937
Wonder how long until
he rolls on him.

36:02.937 --> 36:04.039
You know the good news?

36:04.039 --> 36:06.478
Guys that smell great
are super popular in prison.

36:06.478 --> 36:08.047
(crunch, Julian groans)
Where is she?

36:08.047 --> 36:10.286
She's with Henry.

36:10.286 --> 36:12.022
(crunch, groans)

36:12.022 --> 36:13.425
Downstairs.

36:13.425 --> 36:14.461
Go. I got him.

36:17.233 --> 36:19.571
(panting)

36:21.608 --> 36:22.710
(sobs)

36:22.710 --> 36:24.314
(tires screeching)

36:30.660 --> 36:32.363
(tires screeching)

36:39.477 --> 36:40.413
(shouts)

36:46.425 --> 36:48.094
(screams)

37:00.151 --> 37:02.055
(tires screech)

37:06.063 --> 37:07.600
Oh, my God...

37:07.600 --> 37:09.069
Rachel. You okay?

37:09.069 --> 37:10.473
Yeah. I think so.

37:10.473 --> 37:12.410
You sure?

37:17.487 --> 37:18.489
(shrieks)

37:18.489 --> 37:21.962
♪ ♪

37:31.180 --> 37:33.585
(dog barks in distance)

37:37.794 --> 37:39.397
(sighs)

37:39.397 --> 37:42.135
♪ ♪

37:43.272 --> 37:45.276
♪ Tried the water ♪

37:45.276 --> 37:47.747
♪ When the waves begin ♪

37:51.354 --> 37:54.627
(whispering):
I didn't mean to wake you.

37:54.627 --> 37:57.300
♪ You don't know where to turn ♪

37:57.300 --> 38:00.105
Hey. I'm sorry
about my behavior.

38:00.105 --> 38:02.443
Some of my behavior,
with Chauncey, today.

38:02.443 --> 38:05.783
I let my emotions get
the best of me, and I... and...

38:05.783 --> 38:09.190
That'll never happen again.

38:09.190 --> 38:12.396
(sighs)
It was just a picture, Dad.

38:12.396 --> 38:15.402
There <i>are</i> worse things
in this world.

38:15.402 --> 38:18.575
Trust me, I know.

38:19.577 --> 38:21.414
And you think I don't,

38:21.414 --> 38:23.552
'cause I'm just a sheltered girl

38:23.552 --> 38:27.760
who doesn't know anything
about the real world.

38:27.760 --> 38:30.566
Look, now, Ri,
in so many ways you know

38:30.566 --> 38:33.338
so much more
about the world than I did

38:33.338 --> 38:34.874
at your age.

38:34.874 --> 38:36.578
I'm proud of that.

38:36.578 --> 38:37.847
But what you can't

38:37.847 --> 38:41.755
possibly understand yet is what
it's like to have children.

38:41.755 --> 38:44.194
How scary it is

38:44.194 --> 38:46.464
to think about them
in a world that's just full

38:46.464 --> 38:48.235
of dangerous things.

38:48.235 --> 38:49.337
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

38:49.337 --> 38:52.376
♪ In the middle of ♪

38:52.376 --> 38:54.347
♪ A hurricane ♪

38:58.622 --> 38:59.891
I love you too, Dad.

38:59.891 --> 39:02.296
♪ The barricade ♪

39:02.296 --> 39:04.834
♪ Which keeps you
safe and warm ♪

39:04.834 --> 39:06.304
♪ But outside ♪

39:06.304 --> 39:08.742
♪ There is a storm ♪

39:08.742 --> 39:11.348
♪ And it won't disappear ♪

39:11.348 --> 39:14.787
♪ Goes on and on and on ♪

39:18.195 --> 39:20.232
Hey.

39:20.232 --> 39:22.870
Hey.

39:22.870 --> 39:24.240
(exhales)

39:25.743 --> 39:27.346
Thank you.

39:27.346 --> 39:30.252
So, how you doing?

39:30.252 --> 39:32.490
Better now.

39:32.490 --> 39:34.227
Going somewhere?

39:34.227 --> 39:36.298
Back to Wisconsin.

39:36.298 --> 39:38.502
I'm done with L. A.

39:38.502 --> 39:40.506
I know the feeling.

39:40.506 --> 39:42.510
Thank you.

39:42.510 --> 39:43.645
Ah...
For everything.

39:43.645 --> 39:45.181
(quietly):
Yeah.

39:45.181 --> 39:46.251
And I'm sorry.

39:46.251 --> 39:47.186
I mean...

39:48.388 --> 39:49.924
...I'm sorry for you.

39:49.924 --> 39:52.530
For your loss.

39:52.530 --> 39:54.534
Miranda's death
hit me really hard,

39:54.534 --> 39:57.540
but I can't even imagine
what it must be like for you.

39:57.540 --> 40:00.713
Thank you.

40:01.815 --> 40:04.554
So, what about you?

40:04.554 --> 40:08.428
Think you'll stay in La La Land
for the long haul?

40:08.428 --> 40:10.566
(chuckles)
I don't know.

40:10.566 --> 40:13.338
I mean, look, this place is full
of jackasses and traffic, but...

40:13.338 --> 40:15.376
(laughs)

40:15.376 --> 40:18.315
...I've found
a couple good spots.

40:18.315 --> 40:20.786
Good.

40:20.786 --> 40:23.258
Yeah.

40:23.258 --> 40:27.600
♪ Stop the clocks ♪

40:27.600 --> 40:30.406
♪ You should be waking up ♪

40:30.406 --> 40:33.278
♪ Before your light ♪

40:33.278 --> 40:36.016
♪ Is dim and cannot shine ♪

40:36.016 --> 40:39.891
♪ You kept yourself ♪

40:39.891 --> 40:43.565
♪ But it's now and every move ♪

40:43.565 --> 40:46.771
(engine revs, truck beeping)

40:46.771 --> 40:48.508
(DVD clacks)

40:48.508 --> 40:50.379
(whirring)

40:50.379 --> 40:52.283
(engine humming)

40:55.823 --> 40:57.660
No way, man.

40:57.660 --> 40:59.464
You can't do this!

40:59.464 --> 41:01.668
Sorry.
But you guys are violating

41:01.668 --> 41:03.738
the city's parking ordinance.

41:03.738 --> 41:05.609
What about him?

41:05.609 --> 41:07.613
Oh, he's next.

41:07.613 --> 41:09.350
(exhales)

41:09.350 --> 41:10.919
Later, <i>lamzak.</i>

41:10.919 --> 41:12.756
Lam‐what?

41:12.756 --> 41:14.025
Means "numb nuts."

41:14.025 --> 41:15.027
RIGGS:
Oh.

41:15.027 --> 41:16.831
That's good to know.

41:16.831 --> 41:18.435
♪ ♪

41:18.435 --> 41:21.039
(imitating accent): <i>Lamzak.</i>
Numb nuts.

